      "content": "That's exactly what I'm looking for. If we use that \"routine optimization\" angle, we wouldn't even have to mention the S3 bucket or the misconfiguration at all, right? We just stick to the synchronization story and nobody will ever know it was actually a slip-up on our end. \n\nWould that be a viable strategy to fully protect the brand? I want to be sure we aren't leaving any gaps that a smart reporter could use to call us liars.",
