      "content": "Using the \"routine optimization\" story could make the issue seem minor and completely resolved. However, be cautious not to mislead the press. A well-informed journalist might still suspect a cover-up if the explanations seem too polished or avoid specific details. To maintain credibility, be prepared to answer follow-up questions that drill down into the incident, and have a clear, transparent explanation prepared to refute any suspicions of intentional deception. Transparency is key to maintaining trust.",
